350 g Mushroom Ravioli
56 g Baby Spinach
113 g Mushrooms
1 tbsp Cream Sauce Spice Blend
2 unit(s) Cream Cheese
3 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
250 g Mild Italian Sausage, uncased
½ cup Milk*
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add 10 cups water and 1 tbsp salt to a large pot (use same for 4 ppl). Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Meanwhile, thinly slice mushrooms.
Roughly chop spinach.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.

Heat a large oven-proof pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter, then swirl the pan to melt.
Add sausage and mushrooms to the pan. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up sausage and stirring often until mushrooms have softened, and sausage is cooked through, 4-6 min.**

Meanwhile, add ravioli to the boiling water, then reduce heat to medium-high. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 2-3 min.
Drain and return ravioli to the same pot, off heat.

Reduce heat to medium.
Add garlic and Cream Sauce Spice Blend. Cook, stirring often, until fragrant and coats sausage and mushrooms, 1 min.
Add cream cheese and 1/2 cup (1 cup) milk to the pan with sausage and mushrooms. Stir to combine, until sauce thickens slightly, 1-2 min.
Add half the mozzarella. Cook, stirring often, until cheese is melted, 1 min.
Remove the pan from heat.
Season with salt and pepper, to taste.

Add ravioli and spinach to the pan with sauce. Stir carefully, until spinach is wilted, 1 min.
Sprinkle over remaining mozzarella.
Cover ravioli. Cook, until cheese is melted, 1-2 min.

Let bake rest for 2-3 min to cool slightly.
Divide creamy ravioli bake between plates.

If you've opted to add sausage, when the pan is hot, add sausage along with mushrooms. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up sausage and stirring often until mushrooms have softened and sausage is cooked through, 4-6 min.** Follow the rest of the recipe as written.